## Code Style & Standards

### TypeScript
- Use strict TypeScript practices
- Define proper types/interfaces for all props, API responses, and data structures
- Avoid `any` types - use `unknown` if the type is truly unknown
- Use type inference where appropriate but be explicit for public APIs
- Prefer interfaces for object shapes, types for unions/intersections

### React & Next.js
- Use React Server Components by default, Client Components only when needed (use 'use client' directive)
- Prefer async Server Components for data fetching
- Use Next.js App Router conventions (app directory structure)
- Leverage Next.js built-in Image component for optimized images
- Use proper React patterns: hooks, memo, useMemo, useCallback when appropriate
- Implement proper error boundaries for error handling
- Follow React 19 best practices

### Component Structure
- Create reusable, composable components in the `components/` directory
- Use shadcn/ui components from `components/ui/` when available
- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Extract complex logic into custom hooks
- Use proper prop validation with TypeScript
- Follow the component naming convention: PascalCase

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS v4 utility classes for styling
- Follow mobile-first responsive design approach
- Use dark mode variants with the `dark:` prefix
- Maintain consistent spacing using Tailwind's spacing scale
- Use semantic color tokens from the theme configuration
- Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS when possible
- Use `cn()` utility from `lib/utils.ts` for conditional className merging

### File Organization
- Place components in `components/` directory
- UI primitives go in `components/ui/`
- Utility functions go in `lib/`
- API routes go in `app/api/`
- Types/interfaces can go in a `types/` directory or co-located with components
- Use the `@/` alias for imports (configured in tsconfig.json)
- **File Naming Convention**: Component files should use kebab-case (e.g., `chat-interface.tsx` for the ChatInterface component)

